            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a Hindu philosophical treatise and commentary, written from the perspective and expounding upon the doctrine of the Advaita (non-dualism) Vedānta school of philosophy; presented as a dialogue between a master and his student. Manuscript lacks a beginning.</summary>
